# Rule 03: Style

## Language: {{primary_language}}

{{#if (eq primary_language "typescript")}}
- Strict TypeScript: no `any` without explicit comment explaining why
- Use `type` for type aliases, `interface` for object shapes
- Prefer `const` over `let`; never use `var`
- Use optional chaining `?.` and nullish coalescing `??`
{{/if}}
{{#if (eq primary_language "python")}}
- Type hints required on all function signatures
- Use f-strings for string formatting
- Follow PEP 8 naming: `snake_case` for functions, `PascalCase` for classes
- Prefer dataclasses or Pydantic models over plain dicts for structured data
{{/if}}
{{#if (eq primary_language "go")}}
- Follow `gofmt` formatting — run before every commit
- Use explicit error handling — never ignore errors
- Keep functions short; extract helpers over 20 lines
{{/if}}

## General

{{#if linter}}- Linter `{{linter}}` must pass with zero errors before commit{{/if}}
- Functions: single responsibility, ≤ 30 lines
- No commented-out code in commits
- No `console.log` / `print` debug statements in committed code
<!-- bp-generated:end style-rule -->
